.TH plfs_mode 3 "${PACKAGE_STRING}" 
.SH NAME
plfs_mode 
.SH SYNTAX
#include <plfs.h>
.PP
int plfs_mode( const char *path, mode_t *mode );

.SH DESCRIPTION
Query the mode that was used to create the file.  This should only be called on a PLFS file.  

.SH INPUT PARAMETERS
.TP 1i
path
File to query mode for.  This must be a plfs file.
.TP 1i
mode
permissions for file.

.SH RETURN VALUES
Most PLFS functions return 0 or -errno, except write and read
which return the number of bytes or -errno

